483 void Function::stealArgumentListFrom(Function &Src) { 0
484 assert(isDeclaration() && "Expected no references to current arguments"); 0
485 ----
486 // Drop the current arguments, if any, and set the lazy argument bit. ----
487 if (!hasLazyArguments()) { 0
488 assert(llvm::all_of(makeArgArray(Arguments, NumArgs), 0
489 [](const Argument &A) { return A.use_empty(); }) && ----
490 "Expected arguments to be unused in declaration"); ----
491 clearArguments(); 0
492 setValueSubclassData(getSubclassDataFromValue() | (1 << 0)); 0
493 } ----
494 ----
495 // Nothing to steal if Src has lazy arguments. ----
496 if (Src.hasLazyArguments()) 0
497 return; 0
498 ----
499 // Steal arguments from Src, and fix the lazy argument bits. ----
500 assert(arg_size() == Src.arg_size()); 0
501 Arguments = Src.Arguments; 0
502 Src.Arguments = nullptr; 0
503 for (Argument &A : makeArgArray(Arguments, NumArgs)) { 0
504 // FIXME: This does the work of transferNodesFromList inefficiently. ----
505 SmallString<128> Name; 0
506 if (A.hasName()) 0
507 Name = A.getName(); 0
508 if (!Name.empty()) 0
509 A.setName(""); 0
510 A.setParent(this); 0
511 if (!Name.empty()) 0
512 A.setName(Name); 0
513 } 0
514 ----
515 setValueSubclassData(getSubclassDataFromValue() & ~(1 << 0)); 0
516 assert(!hasLazyArguments()); 0
517 Src.setValueSubclassData(Src.getSubclassDataFromValue() | (1 << 0)); 0
518 } ----
519 ----
520 // dropAllReferences() - This function causes all the subinstructions to "let ----
521 // go" of all references that they are maintaining. This allows one to ----
522 // 'delete' a whole class at a time, even though there may be circular ----
523 // references... first all references are dropped, and all use counts go to ----
524 // zero. Then everything is deleted for real. Note that no operations are ----
525 // valid on an object that has "dropped all references", except operator ----
526 // delete. ----
527 // ----

852 /// Find the segment of \c IntrinsicNameTable for intrinsics with the same ----
853 /// target as \c Name, or the generic table if \c Name is not target specific. ----
854 /// ----
855 /// Returns the relevant slice of \c IntrinsicNameTable ----
856 static ArrayRef findTargetSubtable(StringRef Name) { 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
857 assert(Name.startswith("llvm.")); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
858 ----
859 ArrayRef Targets(TargetInfos); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
860 // Drop "llvm." and take the first dotted component. That will be the target ----
861 // if this is target specific. ----
862 StringRef Target = Name.drop_front(5).split('.').first; 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
863 auto It = partition_point( 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
864 Targets, [=](const IntrinsicTargetInfo &TI) { return TI.Name < Target; }); 5 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
865 // We've either found the target or just fall back to the generic set, which ----
866 // is always first. ----
867 const auto &TI = It != Targets.end() && It->Name == Target ? *It : Targets[0]; 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
868 return ArrayRef(&IntrinsicNameTable[1] + TI.Offset, TI.Count); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
869 } ----

871 /// This does the actual lookup of an intrinsic ID which ----
872 /// matches the given function name. ----
873 Intrinsic::ID Function::lookupIntrinsicID(StringRef Name) { 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
874 ArrayRef NameTable = findTargetSubtable(Name); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
875 int Idx = Intrinsic::lookupLLVMIntrinsicByName(NameTable, Name); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
876 if (Idx == -1) 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll

878 ----
879 // Intrinsic IDs correspond to the location in IntrinsicNameTable, but we have ----
880 // an index into a sub-table. ----
881 int Adjust = NameTable.data() - IntrinsicNameTable; 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
882 Intrinsic::ID ID = static_cast(Idx + Adjust); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
883 ----
884 // If the intrinsic is not overloaded, require an exact match. If it is ----
885 // overloaded, require either exact or prefix match. ----
886 const auto MatchSize = strlen(NameTable[Idx]); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
887 assert(Name.size() >= MatchSize && "Expected either exact or prefix match"); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
888 bool IsExactMatch = Name.size() == MatchSize; 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
889 return IsExactMatch || Intrinsic::isOverloaded(ID) ? ID 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll

904 /// Returns a stable mangling for the type specified for use in the name ----
905 /// mangling scheme used by 'any' types in intrinsic signatures. The mangling ----
906 /// of named types is simply their name. Manglings for unnamed types consist ----
907 /// of a prefix ('p' for pointers, 'a' for arrays, 'f_' for functions) ----
908 /// combined with the mangling of their component types. A vararg function ----
909 /// type will have a suffix of 'vararg'. Since function types can contain ----
910 /// other function types, we close a function type mangling with suffix 'f' ----
911 /// which can't be confused with it's prefix. This ensures we don't have ----
912 /// collisions between two unrelated function types. Otherwise, you might ----
913 /// parse ffXX as f(fXX) or f(fX)X. (X is a placeholder for any other type.) ----
914 /// The HasUnnamedType boolean is set if an unnamed type was encountered, ----
915 /// indicating that extra care must be taken to ensure a unique name. ----
916 static std::string getMangledTypeStr(Type *Ty, bool &HasUnnamedType) { 0
917 std::string Result; 0
918 if (PointerType *PTyp = dyn_cast(Ty)) { 0
919 Result += "p" + utostr(PTyp->getAddressSpace()); 0
920 } else if (ArrayType *ATyp = dyn_cast(Ty)) { 0
921 Result += "a" + utostr(ATyp->getNumElements()) + 0
922 getMangledTypeStr(ATyp->getElementType(), HasUnnamedType); 0
923 } else if (StructType *STyp = dyn_cast(Ty)) { 0
924 if (!STyp->isLiteral()) { 0
925 Result += "s_"; 0
926 if (STyp->hasName()) 0
927 Result += STyp->getName(); 0
928 else ----
929 HasUnnamedType = true; 0
930 } else { ----
931 Result += "sl_"; 0
932 for (auto *Elem : STyp->elements()) 0
933 Result += getMangledTypeStr(Elem, HasUnnamedType); 0
934 } ----
935 // Ensure nested structs are distinguishable. ----
936 Result += "s"; 0
937 } else if (FunctionType *FT = dyn_cast(Ty)) { 0
938 Result += "f_" + getMangledTypeStr(FT->getReturnType(), HasUnnamedType); 0
939 for (size_t i = 0; i < FT->getNumParams(); i++) 0
940 Result += getMangledTypeStr(FT->getParamType(i), HasUnnamedType); 0
941 if (FT->isVarArg()) 0
942 Result += "vararg"; 0
943 // Ensure nested function types are distinguishable. ----
944 Result += "f"; 0
945 } else if (VectorType *VTy = dyn_cast(Ty)) { 0
946 ElementCount EC = VTy->getElementCount(); 0
947 if (EC.isScalable()) 0
948 Result += "nx"; 0
949 Result += "v" + utostr(EC.getKnownMinValue()) + 0
950 getMangledTypeStr(VTy->getElementType(), HasUnnamedType); 0
951 } else if (TargetExtType *TETy = dyn_cast(Ty)) { 0
952 Result += "t"; 0
953 Result += TETy->getName(); 0
954 for (Type *ParamTy : TETy->type_params()) 0
955 Result += "_" + getMangledTypeStr(ParamTy, HasUnnamedType); 0
956 for (unsigned IntParam : TETy->int_params()) 0
957 Result += "_" + utostr(IntParam); 0
958 // Ensure nested target extension types are distinguishable. ----
959 Result += "t"; 0
960 } else if (Ty) { 0
961 switch (Ty->getTypeID()) { 0
962 default: llvm_unreachable("Unhandled type"); 0
963 case Type::VoidTyID: Result += "isVoid"; break; 0
964 case Type::MetadataTyID: Result += "Metadata"; break; 0
965 case Type::HalfTyID: Result += "f16"; break; 0
966 case Type::BFloatTyID: Result += "bf16"; break; 0
967 case Type::FloatTyID: Result += "f32"; break; 0
968 case Type::DoubleTyID: Result += "f64"; break; 0
969 case Type::X86_FP80TyID: Result += "f80"; break; 0
970 case Type::FP128TyID: Result += "f128"; break; 0
971 case Type::PPC_FP128TyID: Result += "ppcf128"; break; 0
972 case Type::X86_MMXTyID: Result += "x86mmx"; break; 0
973 case Type::X86_AMXTyID: Result += "x86amx"; break; 0
974 case Type::IntegerTyID: 0
975 Result += "i" + utostr(cast(Ty)->getBitWidth()); 0
976 break; 0
977 } ----
978 } ----
979 return Result; 0
980 } ----

994 static std::string getIntrinsicNameImpl(Intrinsic::ID Id, ArrayRef Tys, 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
995 Module *M, FunctionType *FT, ----
996 bool EarlyModuleCheck) { ----
997 ----
998 assert(Id < Intrinsic::num_intrinsics && "Invalid intrinsic ID!"); 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
999 assert((Tys.empty() || Intrinsic::isOverloaded(Id)) && 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1000 "This version of getName is for overloaded intrinsics only"); ----
1001 (void)EarlyModuleCheck; ----
1002 assert((!EarlyModuleCheck || M || 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1003 !any_of(Tys, [](Type *T) { return isa(T); })) && ----
1004 "Intrinsic overloading on pointer types need to provide a Module"); ----
1005 bool HasUnnamedType = false; 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1006 std::string Result(Intrinsic::getBaseName(Id)); 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1007 for (Type *Ty : Tys) 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1008 Result += "." + getMangledTypeStr(Ty, HasUnnamedType); 0
1009 if (HasUnnamedType) { 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1010 assert(M && "unnamed types need a module"); 0
1011 if (!FT) 0
1012 FT = Intrinsic::getType(M->getContext(), Id, Tys); 0
1013 else ----
1014 assert((FT == Intrinsic::getType(M->getContext(), Id, Tys)) && 0
1015 "Provided FunctionType must match arguments"); ----
1016 return M->getUniqueIntrinsicName(Result, Id, FT); 0
1017 } ----
1018 return Result; 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1019 } 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll

1265 void Intrinsic::getIntrinsicInfoTableEntries(ID id, 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1266 SmallVectorImpl &T){ ----
1267 // Check to see if the intrinsic's type was expressible by the table. ----
1268 unsigned TableVal = IIT_Table[id-1]; 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1269 ----
1270 // Decode the TableVal into an array of IITValues. ----
1271 SmallVector IITValues; 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1272 ArrayRef IITEntries; 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1273 unsigned NextElt = 0; 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1274 if ((TableVal >> 31) != 0) { 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1275 // This is an offset into the IIT_LongEncodingTable. ----
1276 IITEntries = IIT_LongEncodingTable; 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1277 ----
1278 // Strip sentinel bit. ----
1279 NextElt = (TableVal << 1) >> 1; 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1280 } else { ----
1281 // Decode the TableVal into an array of IITValues. If the entry was encoded ----
1282 // into a single word in the table itself, decode it now. ----
1283 do { ----
1284 IITValues.push_back(TableVal & 0xF); 0
1285 TableVal >>= 4; 0
1286 } while (TableVal); 0
1287 ----
1288 IITEntries = IITValues; 0
1289 NextElt = 0; 0
1290 } ----
1291 ----
1292 // Okay, decode the table into the output vector of IITDescriptors. ----
1293 DecodeIITType(NextElt, IITEntries, IIT_Done, T); 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1294 while (NextElt != IITEntries.size() && IITEntries[NextElt] != 0) 52 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1295 DecodeIITType(NextElt, IITEntries, IIT_Done, T); 39 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1296 } 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll

1298 static Type *DecodeFixedType(ArrayRef &Infos, 0
1299 ArrayRef Tys, LLVMContext &Context) { ----
1300 using namespace Intrinsic; ----
1301 ----
1302 IITDescriptor D = Infos.front(); 0
1303 Infos = Infos.slice(1); 0
1304 ----
1305 switch (D.Kind) { 0
1306 case IITDescriptor::Void: return Type::getVoidTy(Context); 0
1307 case IITDescriptor::VarArg: return Type::getVoidTy(Context); 0
1308 case IITDescriptor::MMX: return Type::getX86_MMXTy(Context); 0
1309 case IITDescriptor::AMX: return Type::getX86_AMXTy(Context); 0
1310 case IITDescriptor::Token: return Type::getTokenTy(Context); 0
1311 case IITDescriptor::Metadata: return Type::getMetadataTy(Context); 0
1312 case IITDescriptor::Half: return Type::getHalfTy(Context); 0
1313 case IITDescriptor::BFloat: return Type::getBFloatTy(Context); 0
1314 case IITDescriptor::Float: return Type::getFloatTy(Context); 0
1315 case IITDescriptor::Double: return Type::getDoubleTy(Context); 0
1316 case IITDescriptor::Quad: return Type::getFP128Ty(Context); 0
1317 case IITDescriptor::PPCQuad: return Type::getPPC_FP128Ty(Context); 0
1318 case IITDescriptor::AArch64Svcount: 0
1319 return TargetExtType::get(Context, "aarch64.svcount"); 0
1320 ----
1321 case IITDescriptor::Integer: 0
1322 return IntegerType::get(Context, D.Integer_Width); 0
1323 case IITDescriptor::Vector: 0
1324 return VectorType::get(DecodeFixedType(Infos, Tys, Context), 0
1325 D.Vector_Width); 0
1326 case IITDescriptor::Pointer: 0
1327 return PointerType::get(Context, D.Pointer_AddressSpace); 0
1328 case IITDescriptor::Struct: { 0
1329 SmallVector Elts; 0
1330 for (unsigned i = 0, e = D.Struct_NumElements; i != e; ++i) 0
1331 Elts.push_back(DecodeFixedType(Infos, Tys, Context)); 0
1332 return StructType::get(Context, Elts); 0
1333 } 0
1334 case IITDescriptor::Argument: 0
1335 return Tys[D.getArgumentNumber()]; 0
1336 case IITDescriptor::ExtendArgument: { 0
1337 Type *Ty = Tys[D.getArgumentNumber()]; 0
1338 if (VectorType *VTy = dyn_cast(Ty)) 0
1339 return VectorType::getExtendedElementVectorType(VTy); 0
1340 ----
1341 return IntegerType::get(Context, 2 * cast(Ty)->getBitWidth()); 0
1342 } ----
1343 case IITDescriptor::TruncArgument: { 0
1344 Type *Ty = Tys[D.getArgumentNumber()]; 0
1345 if (VectorType *VTy = dyn_cast(Ty)) 0
1346 return VectorType::getTruncatedElementVectorType(VTy); 0
1347 ----
1348 IntegerType *ITy = cast(Ty); 0
1349 assert(ITy->getBitWidth() % 2 == 0); 0
1350 return IntegerType::get(Context, ITy->getBitWidth() / 2); 0
1351 } ----
1352 case IITDescriptor::Subdivide2Argument: 0
1353 case IITDescriptor::Subdivide4Argument: { ----
1354 Type *Ty = Tys[D.getArgumentNumber()]; 0
1355 VectorType *VTy = dyn_cast(Ty); 0
1356 assert(VTy && "Expected an argument of Vector Type"); 0
1357 int SubDivs = D.Kind == IITDescriptor::Subdivide2Argument ? 1 : 2; 0
1358 return VectorType::getSubdividedVectorType(VTy, SubDivs); 0
1359 } ----
1360 case IITDescriptor::HalfVecArgument: 0
1361 return VectorType::getHalfElementsVectorType(cast( 0
1362 Tys[D.getArgumentNumber()])); 0
1363 case IITDescriptor::SameVecWidthArgument: { 0
1364 Type *EltTy = DecodeFixedType(Infos, Tys, Context); 0
1365 Type *Ty = Tys[D.getArgumentNumber()]; 0
1366 if (auto *VTy = dyn_cast(Ty)) 0
1367 return VectorType::get(EltTy, VTy->getElementCount()); 0
1368 return EltTy; 0
1369 } ----
1370 case IITDescriptor::VecElementArgument: { 0
1371 Type *Ty = Tys[D.getArgumentNumber()]; 0
1372 if (VectorType *VTy = dyn_cast(Ty)) 0
1373 return VTy->getElementType(); 0
1374 llvm_unreachable("Expected an argument of Vector Type"); 0
1375 } ----
1376 case IITDescriptor::VecOfBitcastsToInt: { 0
1377 Type *Ty = Tys[D.getArgumentNumber()]; 0
1378 VectorType *VTy = dyn_cast(Ty); 0
1379 assert(VTy && "Expected an argument of Vector Type"); 0
1380 return VectorType::getInteger(VTy); 0
1381 } ----
1382 case IITDescriptor::VecOfAnyPtrsToElt: 0
1383 // Return the overloaded type (which determines the pointers address space) ----
1384 return Tys[D.getOverloadArgNumber()]; 0
1385 } ----
1386 llvm_unreachable("unhandled"); 0
1387 } ----
1388 ----
1389 FunctionType *Intrinsic::getType(LLVMContext &Context, 0
1390 ID id, ArrayRef Tys) { ----
1391 SmallVector Table; 0
1392 getIntrinsicInfoTableEntries(id, Table); 0
1393 ----
1394 ArrayRef TableRef = Table; 0
1395 Type *ResultTy = DecodeFixedType(TableRef, Tys, Context); 0
1396 ----
1397 SmallVector ArgTys; 0
1398 while (!TableRef.empty()) 0
1399 ArgTys.push_back(DecodeFixedType(TableRef, Tys, Context)); 0
1400 ----
1401 // DecodeFixedType returns Void for IITDescriptor::Void and IITDescriptor::VarArg ----
1402 // If we see void type as the type of the last argument, it is vararg intrinsic ----
1403 if (!ArgTys.empty() && ArgTys.back()->isVoidTy()) { 0
1404 ArgTys.pop_back(); 0
1405 return FunctionType::get(ResultTy, ArgTys, true); 0
1406 } ----
1407 return FunctionType::get(ResultTy, ArgTys, false); 0
1408 } 0

1413 #undef GET_INTRINSIC_OVERLOAD_TABLE ----
1414 } ----

1421 Function *Intrinsic::getDeclaration(Module *M, ID id, ArrayRef Tys) { 0
1422 // There can never be multiple globals with the same name of different types, ----
1423 // because intrinsics must be a specific type. ----
1424 auto *FT = getType(M->getContext(), id, Tys); 0
1425 return cast( 0
1426 M->getOrInsertFunction( 0
1427 Tys.empty() ? getName(id) : getName(id, Tys, M, FT), FT) 0
1428 .getCallee()); 0
1429 } ----

1432 #define GET_LLVM_INTRINSIC_FOR_CLANG_BUILTIN ----

1436 // This defines the "Intrinsic::getIntrinsicForMSBuiltin()" method. ----
1437 #define GET_LLVM_INTRINSIC_FOR_MS_BUILTIN ----

1439 #undef GET_LLVM_INTRINSIC_FOR_MS_BUILTIN ----

1441 using DeferredIntrinsicMatchPair = ----
1442 std::pair>; ----
1443 ----
1444 static bool matchIntrinsicType( 52 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1445 Type *Ty, ArrayRef &Infos, ----
1446 SmallVectorImpl &ArgTys, ----
1447 SmallVectorImpl &DeferredChecks, ----
1448 bool IsDeferredCheck) { ----
1449 using namespace Intrinsic; ----
1450 ----
1451 // If we ran out of descriptors, there are too many arguments. ----
1452 if (Infos.empty()) return true; 52 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1453 ----
1454 // Do this before slicing off the 'front' part ----
1455 auto InfosRef = Infos; 52 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1456 auto DeferCheck = [&DeferredChecks, &InfosRef](Type *T) { 0
1457 DeferredChecks.emplace_back(T, InfosRef); 0
1458 return false; 0
1459 }; 52 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1460 ----
1461 IITDescriptor D = Infos.front(); 52 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1462 Infos = Infos.slice(1); 52 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1463 ----
1464 switch (D.Kind) { 52 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1465 case IITDescriptor::Void: return !Ty->isVoidTy(); 13 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1466 case IITDescriptor::VarArg: return true; 0
1467 case IITDescriptor::MMX: return !Ty->isX86_MMXTy(); 0
1468 case IITDescriptor::AMX: return !Ty->isX86_AMXTy(); 0
1469 case IITDescriptor::Token: return !Ty->isTokenTy(); 0
1470 case IITDescriptor::Metadata: return !Ty->isMetadataTy(); 39 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1471 case IITDescriptor::Half: return !Ty->isHalfTy(); 0
1472 case IITDescriptor::BFloat: return !Ty->isBFloatTy(); 0
1473 case IITDescriptor::Float: return !Ty->isFloatTy(); 0
1474 case IITDescriptor::Double: return !Ty->isDoubleTy(); 0
1475 case IITDescriptor::Quad: return !Ty->isFP128Ty(); 0
1476 case IITDescriptor::PPCQuad: return !Ty->isPPC_FP128Ty(); 0
1477 case IITDescriptor::Integer: return !Ty->isIntegerTy(D.Integer_Width); 0
1478 case IITDescriptor::AArch64Svcount: 0
1479 return !isa(Ty) || 0
1480 cast(Ty)->getName() != "aarch64.svcount"; 0
1481 case IITDescriptor::Vector: { 0
1482 VectorType *VT = dyn_cast(Ty); 0
1483 return !VT || VT->getElementCount() != D.Vector_Width || 0
1484 matchIntrinsicType(VT->getElementType(), Infos, ArgTys, 0
1485 DeferredChecks, IsDeferredCheck); 0
1486 } ----
1487 case IITDescriptor::Pointer: { 0
1488 PointerType *PT = dyn_cast(Ty); 0
1489 return !PT || PT->getAddressSpace() != D.Pointer_AddressSpace; 0
1490 } ----
1491 ----
1492 case IITDescriptor::Struct: { 0
1493 StructType *ST = dyn_cast(Ty); 0
1494 if (!ST || !ST->isLiteral() || ST->isPacked() || 0
1495 ST->getNumElements() != D.Struct_NumElements) 0
1496 return true; 0
1497 ----
1498 for (unsigned i = 0, e = D.Struct_NumElements; i != e; ++i) 0
1499 if (matchIntrinsicType(ST->getElementType(i), Infos, ArgTys, 0
1500 DeferredChecks, IsDeferredCheck)) ----
1501 return true; 0
1502 return false; 0
1503 } ----
1504 ----
1505 case IITDescriptor::Argument: 0
1506 // If this is the second occurrence of an argument, ----
1507 // verify that the later instance matches the previous instance. ----
1508 if (D.getArgumentNumber() < ArgTys.size()) 0
1509 return Ty != ArgTys[D.getArgumentNumber()]; 0
1510 ----
1511 if (D.getArgumentNumber() > ArgTys.size() || 0
1512 D.getArgumentKind() == IITDescriptor::AK_MatchType) 0
1513 return IsDeferredCheck || DeferCheck(Ty); 0
1514 ----
1515 assert(D.getArgumentNumber() == ArgTys.size() && !IsDeferredCheck && 0
1516 "Table consistency error"); ----
1517 ArgTys.push_back(Ty); 0
1518 ----
1519 switch (D.getArgumentKind()) { 0
1520 case IITDescriptor::AK_Any: return false; // Success 0
1521 case IITDescriptor::AK_AnyInteger: return !Ty->isIntOrIntVectorTy(); 0
1522 case IITDescriptor::AK_AnyFloat: return !Ty->isFPOrFPVectorTy(); 0
1523 case IITDescriptor::AK_AnyVector: return !isa(Ty); 0
1524 case IITDescriptor::AK_AnyPointer: return !isa(Ty); 0
1525 default: break; 0
1526 } ----
1527 llvm_unreachable("all argument kinds not covered"); 0
1528 ----
1529 case IITDescriptor::ExtendArgument: { 0
1530 // If this is a forward reference, defer the check for later. ----
1531 if (D.getArgumentNumber() >= ArgTys.size()) 0
1532 return IsDeferredCheck || DeferCheck(Ty); 0
1533 ----
1534 Type *NewTy = ArgTys[D.getArgumentNumber()]; 0
1535 if (VectorType *VTy = dyn_cast(NewTy)) 0
1536 NewTy = VectorType::getExtendedElementVectorType(VTy); 0
1537 else if (IntegerType *ITy = dyn_cast(NewTy)) 0
